public:
    int x;
    int y;

    MyClass(int newX, int newY) : x(newX), y(newY) { // Fixed: order in the initialization list matches declaration order
        // Constructor body
    }
};
```

Now the initialization list `: x(newX), y(newY)` matches the member variable declaration order in the class: `int x;` followed by `int y;`. Consequently, the `-Wreorder` warning will not be issued for this constructor.

It is a good practice to maintain consistency between the declaration order of member variables and their order in the initialization list to avoid such warnings and ensure clear and understandable code.

